assistantMessages:
I'll fetch Bitcoin hashrate and dominance metrics using the GMX oracle API, which provides real-time price data for crypto assets.

```typescript
const response = await fetch('https://arbitrum-api.gmxinfra.io/prices/tickers');
const tickers = await response.json();

// Find BTC ticker
const btcTicker = tickers.find((t: any) => t.tokenSymbol === 'BTC' || t.tokenSymbol === 'WBTC');

if (!btcTicker) {
  console.log('BTC ticker not found');
  console.log('Available tokens:', tickers.map((t: any) => t.tokenSymbol).join(', '));
} else {
  // Prices are scaled to 30 decimals
  const PRICE_DECIMALS = 30;
  const minPrice = Number(BigInt(btcTicker.minPrice)) / Math.pow(10, PRICE_DECIMALS);
  const maxPrice = Number(BigInt(btcTicker.maxPrice)) / Math.pow(10, PRICE_DECIMALS);
  const midPrice = (minPrice + maxPrice) / 2;

  console.log('=== Bitcoin Price Data from GMX Oracle ===');
  console.log(`Token Symbol: ${btcTicker.tokenSymbol}`);
  console.log(`Token Address: ${btcTicker.tokenAddress}`);
  console.log(`Min Price: $${minPrice.toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 })}`);
  console.log(`Max Price: $${maxPrice.toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 })}`);
  console.log(`Mid Price: $${midPrice.toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 })}`);
  console.log(`Spread: $${(maxPrice - minPrice).toLocaleString('en-US', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 })}`);
  console.log(`Oracle Decimals: ${btcTicker.oracleDecimals}`);
  console.log(`Last Updated: ${new Date(btcTicker.updatedAt * 1000).toISOString()}`);
}

// Also fetch markets info to get BTC open interest on GMX
const marketsResponse = await fetch('https://arbitrum-api.gmxinfra.io/markets/info');
const marketsData = await marketsResponse.json();

// Find BTC markets
const btcMarkets = marketsData.markets?.filter((m: any) => 
  m.name?.includes('BTC') || m.name?.includes('WBTC')
) || [];

if (btcMarkets.length > 0) {
  console.log('\n=== BTC Markets on GMX (Arbitrum) ===');
  btcMarkets.forEach((market: any) => {
    console.log(`\nMarket: ${market.name}`);
    if (market.longInterestUsd) {
      const longOI = Number(BigInt(market.longInterestUsd)) / 1e30;
      console.log(`Long OI: $${longOI.toLocaleString('en-US', { maximumFractionDigits: 0 })}`);
    }
    if (market.shortInterestUsd) {
      const shortOI = Number(BigInt(market.shortInterestUsd)) / 1e30;
      console.log(`Short OI: $${shortOI.toLocaleString('en-US', { maximumFractionDigits: 0 })}`);
    }
  });
}
```

The GMX oracle API provides **real-time price data** but does not include Bitcoin network metrics like hashrate or market dominance — those come from blockchain analytics providers (e.g., Glassnode, CoinGecko, CoinMarketCap).

Here's what the GMX skill **can** provide for Bitcoin:

| Metric | Source | Available |
|--------|--------|-----------|
| BTC/USD spot price | GMX Oracle | ✅ |
| BTC open interest (longs/shorts) | GMX Markets API | ✅ |
| BTC perpetual funding rate | GMX Markets API | ✅ |
| BTC hashrate | Bitcoin network data | ❌ |
| BTC dominance (% of total crypto market cap) | CoinGecko/CMC | ❌ |

**For hashrate and dominance**, you'd need:
- **Hashrate**: [blockchain.com/charts/hash-rate](https://www.blockchain.com/charts/hash-rate) or Glassnode API
- **Dominance**: CoinGecko `/global` endpoint returns `bitcoin_dominance_percentage`

Would you like me to instead show you **BTC trading metrics available on GMX** — such as current price, open interest breakdown, funding rates, or pool utilization?

