I'll set a limit buy (long) for ETH at $2,800 on GMX V2. Let me walk through the setup.

## Setting a Limit Long for ETH at $2,800

### How It Works

A **LimitIncrease** order on GMX triggers when the oracle price drops to or below your trigger price. The keeper executes it once ETH reaches $2,800.

### Code

```typescript
const { GmxSdk } = require("@gmx-io/sdk");
const { createWalletClient, http } = require("viem");
const { privateKeyToAccount } = require("viem/accounts");
const { arbitrum } = require("viem/chains");

async function setEthLimitBuy() {
  // ── Setup ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  const account = privateKeyToAccount(process.env.PRIVATE_KEY);

  const sdk = new GmxSdk({
    chainId: 42161,
    rpcUrl: "https://arb1.arbitrum.io/rpc",
    oracleUrl: "https://arbitrum-api.gmxinfra.io",
    subsquidUrl: "https://gmx.squids.live/gmx-synthetics-arbitrum:prod/api/graphql",
    account: account.address,
    walletClient: createWalletClient({
      account,
      chain: arbitrum,
      transport: http("https://arb1.arbitrum.io/rpc"),
    }),
  });

  // ── Resolve addresses ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  const { marketsInfoData, tokensData } = await sdk.markets.getMarketsInfo();

  // Find the ETH/USD perpetual market (WETH index, not spot-only)
  const ethMarket = Object.values(marketsInfoData).find(
    (m) => tokensData[m.indexTokenAddress]?.symbol === "WETH" && !m.isSpotOnly
  );
  if (!ethMarket) throw new Error("ETH/USD market not found");

  const marketAddress = ethMarket.marketTokenAddress;
  const wethAddress   = ethMarket.longTokenAddress;   // WETH as collateral for longs
  const usdcAddress   = Object.values(tokensData)
    .find((t) => t.symbol === "USDC")?.address;
  if (!usdcAddress) throw new Error("USDC not found");

  // ── Limit price: $2800 scaled to 30 decimals ───────────────────────────────
  // GMX prices use 30-decimal precision: $2800 = 2800 * 10^30
  const limitPrice = 2800n * 10n ** 30n;

  // ── Place the limit long ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  // Paying 100 USDC collateral at 3x leverage → ~$300 position size
  // Order fills when ETH oracle price <= $2800
  const tx = await sdk.orders.long({
    marketAddress,
    payTokenAddress:        usdcAddress,  // paying with USDC
    collateralTokenAddress: wethAddress,  // WETH collateral (standard for longs)
    payAmount:              100_000000n,  // 100 USDC (6 decimals)
